<p>A practical hedge must also work <strong>after costs</strong>: taxes, storage, insurance, fund fees, spreads, and opportunity cost. If gold doubles over a decade while the price level also doubles, it has preserved purchasing power—but it has not created real wealth. That may still be useful, but it is not the same as a productive investment.</p>
